<HEADLINE>
FRATELLO OUT; CLIPPERS TALK TO THOMPSON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Clippers' head coaching wish list lost a
charter member Tuesday night when Mike Fratello, presumed by some
to be the lead suspect, said he no longer is a contender.
</P>
<P>
   On TNT's New York Knicks vs. Indiana Pacers pre-game show from
Indianapolis, Fratello was asked about his status vis--vis the
Clippers job.
</P>
<P>
   He admitted there have been phone discussions with team
representatives,'' but quickly added, ``I won't be involved with
the Clippers. That's not going to work out.''
</P>
<P>
   With Fratello down - one team source said the ``Czar of the
Telestrator'' never was a serious possibility - the next name in
line is that of former Georgetown University coach John Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   According to a statement released by the team, an exploratory
meeting between the Clippers and Thompson regarding the vacant
head-coaching position was held Tuesday. No other information was
available.
</P>
<P>
   Thompson, who coached Patrick Ewing and the Hoyas to the NCAA
Championship in 1984, has been a friend of Elgin Baylor, the Clips'
vice president of basketball operations, since they were kids
growing up in Washington, D.C.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
