<SLUG> BC-HKN-BELFOUR-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BELFOUR GETTING BETTER IN STANLEY CUP DRIVE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHAREAN WILLIAMS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ A long time ago, the Dallas Stars learned that where
there's Ed Belfour, there's a way.
</P>
<P>
   It was Belfour who willed the Stars to victory again Tuesday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Belfour made 29 saves, many of them at point-blank range, in the
Stars' 3-2 overtime victory in Game 5 of the Western Conference
Finals.
</P>
<P>
   ``Eddie played great,'' Stars defenseman Richard Matvichuk said.
``He's played great all playoffs. Everybody knows that goaltending
wins championships, and what he's done for us so far. Hopefully he
can just keep doing it.''
</P>
<P>
   Belfour wasn't one of the three finalists for the Vezina Trophy,
but his name should be the early favorite for the Conn Smythe. No
one has played better in the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's sad not to see his name somewhere near a trophy,'' Stars
center Guy Carbonneau said. ``But Eddie doesn't care about awards.
He cares about the Stanley Cup.''
</P>
<P>
   The Stars have been outshot, 150-114, in the series, yet they
are one victory from returning to the Stanley Cup Finals. The
reason? Belfour. He has made 141 saves in the series for a .940
save percentage.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's stopped a lot of pucks, and that's what we need,'' Stars
forward Mike Keane said. ``He's really saved our bacon several
times. When you get outshot by 15 or more and still win, that
really says something about your goalie.''
</P>
<P>
   In the past three games, the Stars have been outshot, 110-56.
Yet, they have won twice.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday night, the Avalanche fired 31 pucks at Belfour,
including four in overtime. Avalanche center Joe Sakic twice was
turned back by Belfour in overtime, including once in a one-on-one
situation after a Dave Andreychuk slap shot.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just was trying to focus on the puck,'' Belfour said.
``That's my job to come up with the big saves. I got a couple of
saves there and got maybe a little lucky, and you need that.''
</P>
<P>
   In a midseason conference call, Belfour said he was ``as good as
Patrick or better'' when responding to a question about how he
rates himself against Colorado goalie Patrick Roy. So far, Belfour
has been better.
</P>
<P>
   Although he has two shutouts, Roy has allowed 10 goals on only
114 shots.
</P>
<P>
   ``Eddie's playing outstanding,'' Stars center Mike Modano said.
``He's tremendous and getting stronger every game and really
keeping it tight. The games that we lost, we still were in it until
the last minute of the game. To get a lead, he's that much tougher
to beat.''
</P>
<P>
   Until it's over, Belfour will not rest.
</P>
<P>
   ``We still have to win another game,'' Belfour said. ``That's
going to take a lot of hard work.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
