<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _CINCINNATI _ Rev. Fred Shuttlesworth, the leader
of the civil rights movement in Birmingham, Ala., doesn't hesitate
to describe being beaten with bicycle chains and baseball bats by
an angry mob while trying to enroll his daughters in the all-white
Phillips High School. Yet this man often described as ``fiery'' and
``fearless,'' seems pained by the effort of remembering the funeral
of Carole Robertson, one of four girls killed in the Sept. 15,
