<P>
   WITH: DINING _ Has anyone looked at the column to the right of
the entrees at restaurants lately? Crazy numbers! Entrees used to
hover politely under $30, with maybe a lobster or prime sirloin
thrusting boldly beyond that old psychic and budget barrier,
$29.95. Now you see menus with hardly anything under $30. (Marin,
N.Y. Times News Service)
