   TV-LOOKBACK _ So, another network TV season has come and gone.
And what did we learn? Viewers can't get enough of Regis, millions
will watch two strangers get hitched on television and most
comedies still stink. It was, without question, ``The Year of the
Drama.'' West Wing. Once and Again. Family Law. Third Watch.
Judging Amy. Roswell. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   TV-AWARDS _ What were they thinking? Networks make dumb moves
all the time ... so do TV stars. NBC for ever allowing the
no-talent Elle Macpherson to guest-star on Friends. Stick to the
runways, honey, where you don't have to talk. CBS for bringing
JonBenet's grisly murder to television in Perfect Murder, Perfect
Town. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post)
