 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
 &HT;    Fax machine saves its owners money
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ A new fax machine from Sharp Document and Network
Systems of America can cut the cost of running a home business by
finding the cheapest available phone company to handle any fax or
telephone call to another state.
</P>
<P>
   The UX-345L is one of the first fax machines on the market to
utilize low-cost routing technology, according to a press release
from the office product division of Sharp Electronics Corp. The
product is made possible by a collaboration between Sharp and
openLCR.com, a Web-based telecommunications company.
</P>
<P>
   When you buy the UX-345L, you link the machine to the
openLCR.com Web site to prepare it to work. From the site, the fax
machine downloads a listing of all pricing information for the
available long-distance companies to a chip in the machine.
</P>
<P>
   When the user dials an area code and the first three digits of
the number being called, the UX-345L checks its list and picks the
company with the lowest rate for that day of the week and time of
day.
</P>
<P>
   Users don't have to remember access codes for different
long-distance services or sign up with new long-distance carriers.
They also retain their current telephone billing system; the calls
directed by the UX-345L will be itemized on the customers' regular
phone bills.
</P>
<P>
   The machine links to the openLCR.com Web site once a month to
get the latest rate information.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the low-cost routing feature, the UX-345L has all
the bells and whistles found on other moderately priced plain-paper
fax machines.
</P>
<P>
   It has a 60-sheet paper cassette and about 28 pages of built-in
memory that can store incoming faxes when the paper cassette is
empty.
</P>
<P>
   The UX-345L has distinctive ring detection that allows up to
four telephone numbers to ring on one telephone line, a caller ID
that displays the name and number of the caller, anti-junk fax
settings to block unwanted transmissions and a copier function.
</P>
<P>
   It includes a 10-page document feeder and an automatic cover
sheet writer, and it transmits an average page in about 15 seconds.
</P>
<P>
   The UX-345L sells for $129.99 at www.sharpoffice.com, and it's
available where office supplies are sold. For additional
information, call Sharp at (800) 237-4277 (BE-SHARP) or log on to
the www.sharpoffice.com site.
</P>
<P>
   For additional information on the low-cost routing service,
visit www.openLCR.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
