   MUSIC-COPYRIGHT (Undated) _ A brief amendment to the copyright
law has pitted musicians against recording companies over the
question of who owns recordings: the companies that finance and
market them or the musicians who perform them. At stake is control
over recordings starting 35 years after they were first released,
when many of them are still extremely valuable. By Jon Pareles.
</P>
