internationally, particularly in the Middle East and Asia. (Poole,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   UNITED _ United formally announces its planned buyout of US
Airways. Following developments with an eye toward where this
leaves Delta. Its interest in Continental might be rekindled,
except that Northwest's ownership of a sizable stake in CO poses a
major problem. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HOME-DEPOT-IXL _ It appears the relationship between iXL
Enterprises and Home Depot, glowingly touted in November as a coup
for the website developer and the beginning of Home Depot's
redefining of e-commerce, is over in 6 months. Home Depots says
only iXL has done what it was hired to do, but the retailer is a
long way from being an e-commerce contender and Home Depot has
nothing to say on how further development will be handled or by
whom. iXL has a different story, saying they are still talking to
Home Depot about continuing the relationship. (Bond/Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   DEPOT-BIAS _ Home Depot is being charged with racial profiling
by a black customer in Los Angeles who said he was falsely arrested
and jailed for a fraudulent refund. Derek Pina said he brought an
original receipt for $12.80 worth of goods, but was handcuffed and
arrested when a security officer claimed the receipt was fake. He
seeks $7 million. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HUDDLE-HOUSE _ Georgia-based Huddle House signs a deal
broadening its presence in Virginia, one of the key states the
company has targeted for growth. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
