<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am trying to find Bridgewater Candles, which are similar to
Yankee Co. Candles.
</P>
<P>
   _ Teresa Hardy, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: When decorating your home, candles make perfect scents. And
Bridgewater Candle Co., which is based in Buffalo, S.C., offers 42
fragrances, from sweet magnolia to vanilla cream and kiwi melon to
apple pie. The long-burning candles are available in small and
large jars as well as pillars, wafers and votives. Prices range
from 89 cents to $18.99. Stores that carry these candles include:
Wildbirds Unlimited in Marietta (770-565-9841), Wicks N Sticks in
Morrow (770-961-4089) and Kathy's Too, also in Marietta
(770-424-6552). For a complete list of stores in Georgia, call
1-877-843-2743. You can also order the candles online at
www.annsfinegifts.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: About two years ago in Buyer's Edge, you featured a collar
that can be worn around your neck _ to cool you off. Wal-Mart
carries one in cloth but it's not too durable.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rajgopal Sashti, Columbus, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: The lightweight aluminum collar that soon will ring your neck
is a wearable air conditioner. You simply fill its two chambers
with a few ounces of water, rest it on your neck and switch it on.
A quiet, tiny fan moves air across the water, cooling the area
around you up to 20 degrees. The flexible sides hold the cooling
plate against your neck _ and you feel cool all over. It weighs 16
ounces filled. It's $49.95 at Sharper Image stores _ in Lenox
Square (404-261-8388) and Mall of Georgia (770-271-1890). The S-M
size is SI528; the L-XL size is SI558. You can also order from the
company catalog: 1-800-344-4444.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Listermint mouthwash. It is one of the few
that is alcohol-free and the only one my husband likes. Eckerd
carried it at one time but no longer has it in stock.
</P>
<P>
   _ Martha Lewis, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   And another mouthwash query: I have been looking for Lavoris
mouthwash for a very long time.
</P>
<P>
   _ Penny Keith, Decatur, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Now you can both eat all the garlic you desire. We found
Listermint Alcohol-Free Mouthwash (32-ounce bottle, $3.99) and
Lavoris (32-ounce bottle, $3.19) at Drug Emporium, 4000 LaVista
Road N.E. at Northlake (770-939-2860). Mint-flavored Listermint
contains no fluoride, while mint-flavored Lavoris comes enhanced
with vitamin C and herbs (sage, thyme, echinacea).
</P>
<P>
   Q: I cannot find a rubber hot water bottle. Recently we had a
power outage at our home but still had hot water. A hot water
bottle would have helped to warm the feet of my paralyzed husband.
Thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Teresa Rigby, Dunwoody, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We found Sunmark's deluxe water bottle _ the 2-quart capacity
bag is $8.68 _ at King's Drugs, 2345 Peachtree Road N.E.
(404-233-2101). You can use this ribbed surface water bottle for
warm or cold application, to soothe muscle aches and pains and warm
cold feet.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Can you help me find Land O'Lakes Country Morning Blend light
in the plastic tub? It is the best margarine I've found and
actually tastes like butter (well, almost!). I used to be able to
buy it at Kroger and at Publix. Now, no one has it anymore. Most
stores carry the higher fat version, called Country Morning Blend.
</P>
<P>
   _ Becki Seddon, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Spread this around. We found your Country Morning Blend ight
at Publix, 2868 Peachtree Road N.W. (404-848-0330). Very few stores
in Atlanta carry it. A 1-pound tub is $1.79. This blend, says the
manufacturer, has 65 percent less saturated fat than butter. Other
crucial info: Country Morning Blend has no cholesterol and 2 grams
saturated fat. Butter, on the other hand, has 30 milligrams of
cholesterol and 7.7 grams of saturated fat.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
