<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   GORE-LABOR _ Vice President Gore will tomorrow find himself
caught in another political struggle involving labor and other
supporters. The AJC has learned that the Hotel Employee and
Restaurant Employee union of Los Angeles, part of LA's powerful
labor movement, plans to begin Thursday a major union organizing
drive at the Loews Santa Monica Hotel. The hotel is owned by
Jonathan Tisch, the chairman of Gore's New York City finance
committee and a $200,000 soft money contributor to the Democratic
Party. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
