<P>
   AIR-MERGER-JOHNSON (Washington) _ United and US Airways are
proposing to hand off the operation at Ronald Reagan National
Airport in Washington to Robert Johnson, the founder of Black
Entertainment Television. The proposed DC Air would begin as a
``virtual airline,'' leasing from United its big planes, complete
with pilots and flight attendants, and buying the time of
mechanics, gate agents, and everyone else needed for a flight,
almost down to the foil-wrapped peanuts. By Steven A. Holmes and
Matthew L. Wald.
