   CISCO-MARKETPLACE (Undated) A vote of confidence from Cisco
Systems can be very important to fledging technology companies,
especially if they have initial public offerings on the horizon.
Just how important? Ask Selectica, a San Jose, Calif., company that
makes software to help businesses sell complex products over the
Internet. Selectica was so eager to make Cisco a customer that in a
recent deal it wound up paying Cisco to take its software. By Alex
Berenson.
