<P>
   UNDATED _ Recipes for a cake that's fluffy and a cake that's
flat. By BEVERLY BUNDY. Story will move in ``d'' food and dining
category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEER NUT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ If you've ever had an occasion to encounter the mud
along the Mississippi, particularly near the delta, you know it
isn't very attractive. After draining about half of the United
States, the river coughs up a gooey, sticky, oily and
chemical-smelling mess. That said, one wonders why someone would
try to sell a beer called Mississippi Mud, particularly when what
we have here is more about gimmicky packaging and marketing than it
is about beer. By PAUL BOURGEOIS. Story will move in ``d'' food and
dining category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ If Hillary Clinton intends to create the perception
that Rick Lazio is a right-wing ideologue who adheres to the gospel
of Newt Gingrich, how will they explain his past support from
environmental activist groups and his vote for the Brady law
regulating purchases of handguns? By the time Election Day rolls
around, Hillary Clinton might be wishing that Rudy Giuliani had
stayed in the race. By BILL THOMPSON. Story will move in ``k''
commentary category &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
