<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Washington) _ In one of the most significant and
hotly debated foreign policy decisions that Congress has faced, the
House votes to grant China permanent normal trading relations,
handing President Clinton a major foreign policy triumph. After an
intense debate that encompassed human rights, protection of
American jobs and national security, the House voted 237-197 in
favor of the bill. By Eric Schmitt and Joseph Kahn. (We plan to
move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
