picturesque military center of the Israeli occupation of southern
Lebanon for two decades. Before noon Wednesday, the morning after
the occupation zone prematurely collapsed, its stores were
shuttered and its cobblestone streets nearly empty but for two
young men with a clipboard. By Deborah Sontag. (Scheduled to move
