The Charlotte beltways have become a Disney-like theme park of car
shops for Nascar teams, drawing tourists as they provide the work
for the best stock-car drivers in the world. By Richard Sandomir.
(Scheduled to move by 8:45 p.m. ET in ``s'' news file.) 1,500
words.
</P>
<P>
   CHILE-PINOCHET (Lima, Peru) _ A Chilean appeals court has
stripped the immunity of retired Gen. Augusto Pinochet, removing an
important obstacle to his possible trial on charges that he was
involved in the kidnapping, murder and torture of thousands during
his 17 years as Chile's dictator. The decision is subject to a
Supreme Court reversal and it could take years of legal wrangling
before any trial could begin. By Clifford Krauss. (The story has
moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Reefer: AIR-MERGER (New York) _ They started talking about a
deal last November, when James Goodwin, chairman and chief
executive of UAL Corp., approached Stephen Wolf, chairman of US
Airways, about buying his airline. For the next six months, those
discussions somehow stayed under wraps, out of the public eye. By
Kenneth N. Gilpin. (Eds.: an early version of this story has moved;
the 1stLd-Writethru is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news
file.) 1,100 words.
</P>
