address is weyded(at)nytimes.com. If unable to reach Ms. Weydert,
please call 800-444-0267, or fax us at 816-822-1444.)  
 &HT;    
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been filed into the ``f'' financial
news, ``a'' domestic/general news and ``l'' lifestyle news
files.)  
 &HT;    
 By TED C. FISHMAN  
 c.2000 Worth Magazine  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
<P>
   Today's leading-edge video games take players through worlds
that go on forever. Just as soon as you think you've solved enough
puzzles, killed enough eight-headed dragons, and disarmed enough
malevolent wizards to conquer and rule, new enemies emerge.
</P>
