   &QL; 
 &UR; VOICE _ &LR;  Diane Paulsen was worried that her vacation in Los Angeles
would be rained out after beginning the drive from San Francisco in
a storm.
</P>
<P>
   To alleviate her concerns, she called the Internet. She spoke to
a computer that understands verbal commands and was ``told'' in an
automated voice that the weather in Southern California was balmy.
 &UR; BY VERNE KOPYTOFF &LR;
