<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-INJURIES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SCRAMBLING BECAUSE OF INJURIES NOT NEW FOR STARS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MAC ENGEL 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Game 6 of the Western Conference Finals isn't
normally the ideal time to search for a second-line winger.
</P>
<P>
   The better time is Game 6 of the regular season.
</P>
<P>
   With winger Jamie Langenbrunner out with an injured right knee,
however, the search is on. Whether it's rookies Roman Lyashenko or
Brenden Morrow, second-year forward Jon Sim or veteran Grant
Marshall, the Stars need a winger to play alongside Scott Thornton
and Joe Nieuwendyk.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've been without him a little bit before, but he's obviously
a big part of the team,'' Thornton said of Langenbrunner. ``He
works so hard. He brings a lot of grit to the line, he's a skilled
guy. He's just a hole in the lineup that is hard to replace.''
</P>
<P>
   The lone bright spot in this for the Stars is that they have
been forced to fill holes all season. So tonight's Game 6 against
the Avalanche is no different.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the only line that will stay the same will be \RMike\S
Modano's line,'' Stars coach Ken Hitchcock said. ``Everything else
will change.''
</P>
<P>
   There is little reason to change the top line of Modano, Brett
Hull and Jere Lehtinen. Modano and Hull] have been on the ice for
eight of the Stars' 10 goals in the series.
</P>
<P>
   Beyond that is where the search starts.
</P>
<P>
   In Langenbrunner's absence, Sim, who played in 25 games during
the regular-season but hasn't played in the playoffs, could move up
to the second line.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a rumor going around I'm going to play,'' said Sim,
who scored five goals with three assists this season and played in
four playoff games last season. ``Of course, I'll be nervous. But
\Rlast year\S helps. It gives me some confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   If Sim isn't inserted in the lineup, Lyashenko could stay on the
second line, where he finished Game 5 after Langenbrunner was hurt
in the first period.
</P>
<P>
   That would likely mean winger Blake Sloan would return to his
spot on the third or fourth line after being a healthy scratch in
Games 4 and 5.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it depends on where we're going to play Jon,''
Hitchcock said. ``I think for Jon to be effective, he's going to
have to be a top-six forward, so he would really just replace
Jamie. If we want to scale it down and play Marshall in that hole
then we could put Sloan in and he could come in as a third- or
fourth-line player.''
</P>
<P>
   The advantage Sim brings is that he's a fast, skilled player
with a solid left-handed shot. The advantage Lyashenko brings is
that he's a skilled center capable of playing wing and has seen
action in the series.
</P>
<P>
   The advantage the Stars have is that they have done this all
season. So, whether it's game No. 66 of the regular season or Game
6 of the Western Conference Finals, search parties are part of the
routine.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-24-00 2341EDT &QL; 
